Israeli Stocks: Elbit Imaging, Mazor, Ness Technologies

-- B y   S h a r o n   W r o b e l
-- 
2011-06-06T10:30:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-06/israeli-stocks-elbit-imaging-mazor-ness-technologies.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index dropped 0.1
percent to 1,228.91 at 12:57 p.m. in  Tel Aviv . Local markets
will be closed on June 7 and June 8 for a holiday.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Elbit Imaging Ltd. (EMIT)   surged to the highest since
June 1, adding 2.7 percent to 24.44 shekels. The investor in
real estate and medical companies said that its board of
directors has resolved not to distribute dividends for at least
the next 12 months to preserve liquidity.  Mazor Robotics Ltd. (MZOR)   rose the most since Feb. 7,
advancing 5.6 percent to 8.51 shekels. The developer of surgical
robots got European CE and the U.S. Food and Drug Administration
approval for the marketing of its Renaissance system, a new
generation of surgical robot replacing the company’s SpineAssist
system.  Ness Technologies Inc. (NSTC)   jumped the most since May
11, gaining 8.9 percent to 21.94 shekels. The computer service
provider is in talks to be acquired by Citi Venture Capital
International, a private equity fund backed by Citigroup Inc.,
Calcalist said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Wrobel in Tel Aviv at 
 swrobel4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
